Notes: The 'row_id' functions as a unique identifier for the ProblemCondition instance. Path 28 links ProblemCondition to an xsd:string identifier, which semantically fits such an ID.

The 'patient_id' corresponds to an identifier of the patient related to the problem condition. Path 23 traverses ProblemCondition to Patient and then to PatientIdentifier, which is the most semantically precise path for patient IDs.

The 'diagnosis_code' represents a code for the problem condition diagnosis. Path 67 extends from ProblemCondition through hasCode to Code's identifier. This is more precise than just linking to Code or Terminology alone.
The 'created_at' column indicates the datetime when the ProblemCondition was recorded. Path 14 directly links ProblemCondition to an xsd:dateTime, matching the timestamp semantics.

The 'org_code' identifies the code of the data provider institute related to the problem condition. Path 79 goes from ProblemCondition to DataProviderInstitute then to Code and its identifier, best representing an organizational code.
The 'org_name' corresponds to the name of the data provider institute. Path 81 maps from ProblemCondition to DataProviderInstitute and then to its name property as xsd:string, which fits perfectly.
